-- Eagle Hospitality to Sell 13 Hotels to Repay Lender
-- B y   B r i a n   L o u i s
-- 2012-09-10T21:30:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-10/eagle-hospitality-to-sell-13-hotels-to-repay-lender.html
Eagle Hospitality Properties Trust
Inc. plans to sell its 13 hotels as part of a deal reached with
a lender that allows the company to pay the debt at a discount.  The properties include the Cincinnati Landmark Marriott and
the Chicago Marriott Southwest in Burr Ridge,  Illinois , Eagle
said today in a statement. The Wall Street Journal reported
earlier today that Eagle, based in Purchase,  New York , and
 Blackstone Group LP (BX)  reached an agreement on the debt.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Louis in Chicago at 
 blouis1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
